I want to evaluate all the output of FusedBatchNorm. The easy way to get it/them is to run the following code sess.run(batch_norm.outputs[:]. I'll get an error in TF 1.10 now:

ipdb> out = sess.run(batch_norm.outputs[:])
*** OutOfRangeError: Node 'MobilenetV2/expanded_conv/depthwise/BatchNorm/FusedBatchNorm' (type: 'Const', num of outputs: 1) does not have output 1

However, if we see the length of batch_norm, it's 5.

body:
I want to evaluate all the output of FusedBatchNorm. The easy way to get it/them is to run the following code `sess.run(batch_norm.outputs[:]`. I'll get an error in TF 1.10 now:
```
ipdb> out = sess.run(batch_norm.outputs[:])
*** OutOfRangeError: Node 'MobilenetV2/expanded_conv/depthwise/BatchNorm/FusedBatchNorm' (type: 'Const', num of outputs: 1) does not have output 1 
```
However,  if we see the length of `batch_norm`, it's `5`.
